<HEADLINE>
FT  11 DEC 92 / International Company News: Inco takes Dollars 16m charge
for cuts
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By KENNETH GOODING
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
INCO, the world's second-biggest nickel producer, will take a USDollars 16m
pre-tax charge in the fourth quarter in respect of 400 job cuts, writes
Kenneth Gooding. The Toronto-based group estimated the move would reduce
employment costs by an annual Dollars 22m. Inco previously took an Dollars
18.8m charge in the third quarter for an early-retirement programme.
</TEXT>
