   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
KNIGHT-RIDDER, the US newspaper group, was near to signing a book publishing
deal that will exploit the company's traditional news-gathering forces, said
Mr Anthony Ridder, president, Reuter reports from New York.
Mr Ridder said Knight-Ridder hoped to sign a deal with a leading US book
