<HEADLINE>
FT  11 DEC 92 / International Company News: The Equitable forms link with
disability insurer
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NIKKI TAIT
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE EQUITABLE, the large but troubled US life insurance company in which
France's Axa has a 49 per cent stake, said yesterday it was forming a
'strategic alliance' with UNUM, a medium-sized insurance company which
specialises in disability insur-ance.
The Equitable, which turned itself from a mutual insurance operation into a
shareholder-owned company earlier this year to boost capital, said the
tie-up was part of a general strategy of concentrating on 'core life
insurance and annuity business'.
Equitable's 8,300-strong agency sales force will sell individual disability
products 'based on product designs, administrative systems and claims
management capabilities developed by UNUM'.
The smaller, Maine-based insurer will reinsure a significant portion of the
insurance risk on these policies. It will also reinsure part of the
insurance risk on Equitable's existing individual disability business.
This arrangement will not include Equitable's open disability claims, but in
these cases UNUM will provide claims management services on a
fee-for-service basis.
</TEXT>
