Mr Chapman, 'by aggressive marketing'. Operating profits edged ahead to
Pounds 9.79m (Pounds 9.71m) because of lower margins, though the figure
included a Pounds 2.3m charge for the closure costs of Matador Paper Mills
and a Pounds 2.17m credit from the sale of the Next stake.
Reduced rates led to a fall in interest charges to Pounds 4.84m (Pounds
5.22m), though the group paid Pounds 4.4m to exercise its final option to
lift its stake in Grattan from 10 to 15 per cent.
Earnings advanced to 4.54p (3.86p) per share and the interim dividend is
raised to 3p (2.7p).
