<HEADLINE>
FT  11 DEC 92 / Directors face ban over safety
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CATHERINE MILTON, Labour Staff
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
BUSINESS CHIEFS who flout health and safety law may be banned from being
company directors and face heavy fines, the Health and Safety Executive
warned yesterday.
Lewes Crown Court, sitting at Hove, East Sussex, disqualified Mr Rodney
Chapman, of Tunbridge Wells, Kent, from being a company director for two
years and fined him Pounds 5,000 in a prosecution brought by the executive
earlier this year.
It was the first time a director has been banned under the 1986 Company
Directors Disqualification Act for breaching health and safety law.
The Health and Safety Commission's annual report, published yesterday, shows
that accidents and ill health at work are costing employers up to Pounds 9bn
a year.
</TEXT>
