<TEXT>
France's central bank yesterday announced a slight easing of its money
supply target for next year, to take account of an expected small pick-up in
economic growth, writes William Dawkins in Paris. The new range for growth
of the M3 measure of broad money will be between 4 per cent and 6.5 per
