set to grow by 6 per cent, right at the top of its 4 per cent to 6 per cent
target for 1992, which Mr de Larosiere attributed to a rise in savings.
He stressed that the central policy objectives would continue to be to
defend the franc's stability and to control inflation, but that enlargement
of the M3 target was justified to give 'every chance' for an economic
recovery.
