<DATE>921210
</DATE>
<HEADLINE>
FT  10 DEC 92 / Survey of Software at Work - Winter 1992 (25): Let us hear
from you - Software at work, Future issues / Events move so fast in the
computer industry that users find themselves faced with an increasing range
of software options
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
SOFTWARE is a management issue.
Nearly two years ago, Software At Work set out with this message, explaining
how technology was being used by individual businessmen and women to benefit
their businesses.
The product reviews contained in the seven issues to date have come from
live users of software products. Through extensive user interviews, stories
of successful (and struggling) business software users have been uncovered,
and through the accompanying 'consultants' critiques,' the reasons for
success (or failure) have been explained.
The Software at Work writing team now wants to hear from you. Below is a
list of areas covered in previous issues of Software At Work, (available on
