FT  10 DEC 92 / Survey of Software at Work - Winter 1992 (12): Company
Snapshot
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Fisher Park Fisher Park was founded in 1977 by its joint directors, and is
based in Kings Cross, London. There are six employees.
Nature of the company's business:
Fisher Park designs spectacular backgrounds for rock tours and other musical
events (such as Pavarotti in the Park), using a mixture of architecture and
engineering. They are one of the leading three-dimensional designers in
their field and are pace-setters in bringing their professional disciplines
to this form of theatre.
Turnover: Pounds 500,000
Key personnel: Two directors - architect Mark Fisher, engineer. Jonathon
Park
TECHNOLOGY FILE
Software: Autodesk's AutoCAD release 11; Animator Pro; 3D Studio
Release 2
Hardware: 3 seats, 2 Dell 386s PC plus one 486 (currently on loan).
Cost of project: Pounds 20,000 inclusive of software and hardware.
Support: The consultancy, Deus Ex Machina implemented the software and
helped with front-end menus tailored to Fisher Park's needs. There has been
no formal software training for anyone in the company.
