<TEXT>
GOLD pared early losses and struggled to hold above Dollars 334 a troy ounce
in late trade, aided by a statement from Hungary's central bank that it had
sold gold in normal market operations and not from reserves. Gold hit a
one-month low fix of Dollars 333.40 on the London bullion market in the
