FT  10 DEC 92 / International Company News: Pirelli warns of further loss
due to recession
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By HAIG SIMONIAN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
PIRELLI, the Italian tyres and cables group, warned that it faced a further
loss this year, before extraordinary items, owing to economic recession and
continuing difficulties in its two main activities.
The warning came after an agreement last Saturday with government ministers
and unions covering almost 1,000 job losses at two tyre plants.
The company had previously cited delays in pushing through the redundancies
as a major obstacle to restored profits. Substantial closures and job losses
have already taken place at some of its foreign operations.
Pirelli made a net profit of L77bn (Dollars 56.2bn) in the first half of
this year after losing L105bn in the same period in 1991. However, it
stressed the 1992 figures were not directly comparable owing to accounting
and consolidation changes.
The precise outcome for 1992 will depend on how much Pirelli realises from
the continuing disposals in its diversified products division, some of which
have already been sold. The company said extraordinary items would be
positive, but their size depended on the outcome of talks on further
disposals.
