<HEADLINE>
FT  10 DEC 92 / UK Company News: Countryside Pounds 11.7m in the red
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
COUNTRYSIDE Properties, the residential, commercial and property company,
unveiled losses before tax of Pounds 11.7m for the 12 months to September
30.
That compared with previous profits of Pounds 3.05m and was struck after
taking account of exceptional provisions of Pounds 14.8m (Pounds 1.2m).
A provision of Pounds 10.1m was made against development sites and there was
also a deficit of Pounds 8.3m arising on a revaluation of the investment
properties.
The latter was partly offset against the revaluation reserve of Pounds 3.6m
with the remainder of the deficit amounting to Pounds 4.7m charged to the
profit and loss account.
Turnover for the year fell to Pounds 79.7m (Pounds 87.1m). The contribution
from the residential side rose to Pounds 70.4m (Pounds 63.6m) while that
from the commercial activity fell to Pounds 3.4m (Pounds 21m). Property
investment income was Pounds 5.9m (Pounds 2.5m).
Pre-exceptional profits from residential fell to Pounds 5.4m (Pounds 6.7m)
while the loss from commercial was cut to Pounds 775,000 (Pounds 2.4m).
Losses per share emerged at 17.3p (earnings 7.2p). A same-again final
dividend of 2.7p is paid from reserves and holds the total at 4.11p.
