<DOCNO>FT924-2885</DOCNO>
<PROFILE>_AN-CLJCGAEMFT</PROFILE>
<DATE>921210
</DATE>
<HEADLINE>
FT  10 DEC 92 / UK Company News: Grainger loses Pounds 4m on provision
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRIS TIGHE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
GRAINGER TRUST, the property investor and trader, yesterday reported a swing
from profits of Pounds 1.37m to losses of Pounds 4.42m pre-tax for the year
to September 30.
The figure was struck after taking account of an exceptional write-down of
Pounds 5.57m on building land.
Tax credits of Pounds 2.5m (Pounds 234,000) left the after-tax deficit at
Pounds 1.92m, compared with a profit of Pounds 1.61m last time.
Losses per share were 9.56p (earnings 8.03p) but a final dividend of 4.05p
makes a same-again 5.25p total.
Trading profits fell by 34 per cent to Pounds 8.68m (Pounds 13.2m) due to
difficult conditions in the housing market. Turnover was also down, at
Pounds 28.7m (Pounds 34.8m).
Gross rentals improved by 8 per cent to Pounds 9.87m thanks to favourable
rent reviews and re-registrations; net cash inflow from operating activities
rose to Pounds 18.4m (Pounds 15.6m).
Mr Stephen Dickinson, managing director, said the group was not
disappointed. 'We think we've done extremely well in a very difficult
period,' he said.
The group has renegotiated bank borrowings, repayable over 15 years to 2007,
of Pounds 92.6m out of a total as at September 30 of Pounds 107.8m. The
group plans a substantial reduction in net borrowings over the next five
years.
Net asset value, adjusted for market value of trading properties, was Pounds
2.93 (Pounds 3.29).
</TEXT>
