<HEADLINE>
FT  10 DEC 92 / Observer: Sugar test
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
For a man who has just signed up Alan Sugar, the establishment's
non-executive headhunter Colin St Johnston is surprisingly reticent about
his plans for his new client.
Although St Johnston's Pro-Ned outfit despises the old boy network which
fills corporate boardrooms, it still prefers to work behind the scenes. It
has helped troubled companies like Wace and Brent Walker find new non-execs,
but finding someone prepared to stand up to Alan Sugar will be an acid test
of its effectiveness.
If St Johnston comes up trumps, he should be able to increase his standard
Pounds 12,000 finder's fee.
</TEXT>
