FT  10 DEC 92 / Letter: Snicker bar gains currency in Russia
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Mr PETER BREEN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, Observer should take comfort ('Basket cases', December 8) that there
have been no Treasury whisperings about the Mars bar as an alternative
currency.
On a visit to Moscow last week, I found that the Moscow Tribune, a daily
free newspaper celebrating its 20th anniversary (20 days, not years, of
uninhibited publication), was running a Snicker index.
Present street kiosk prices for the Snicker chocolate bar are inflating by
20 per cent a week. Travellers to Russia might bear this in mind when
debating which 'currency' to take with them.
Peter Breen,
managing partner,
Heidrick &amp; Struggles Intl,
100 Piccadilly, London W1
