<TEXT>
The Dutch have always semed to me more like the English than any other race.
They often have a similar sense of humour, share a tradition of liberalism
and non-conformism, love the sea and have a splendid maritime tradition, and
stand in similar juxtaposition between the excitable Mediterranean
temperament and the sadder introversion of Scandinavia. We are promised that
The Essential History Of Europe (8.00 BBC2) was filmed in the streets,
galleries, canals and brothels of Amsterdam, with satirical comments from
cabaret artists Joep van Haek. Time was when the commercial television
authority banned hypnotism (with dating agencies, and undertakers) from its
advertising. Today ITV offers an entire 60 minute about The Andrew Newton
Hypnotic Experience (9.00) with members of the audience involved in
'intriguing and often amusing moments'. BBC2 repeats the programme which won
the documentary prize at this year's Prix Italia festival, War, Lives And
Videotape. A one-man effort by Nick Danziger, it shows efforts to re-house
orphans who lived in an asylum in Kabul (9.30).
